Andriy Viktorovych Polunin (; ; born 5 March 1971 in Dnipropetrovsk) is a retired Ukrainian professional footballer. Since 2007 he works as a director of sports with FC Naftovyk-Ukrnafta Okhtyrka.
He made his professional debut in the Soviet Second League in 1989 for FC Shakhtar Pavlohrad.
==Honours==
* Ukrainian Premier League runner-up: 1993
* Ukrainian Premier League bronze: 1992, 1995, 1996, 1998
* Vyscha Liha Footballer of the Year: 1996
